{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1658,"text":"Imagine a place where your neighbors\ngreet your children by name;"},{"time":7628,"text":"a place with splendid vistas;"},{"time":10955,"text":"a place where you can drive\njust 20 minutes"},{"time":14090,"text":"and put your sailboat on the water."},{"time":16680,"text":"It's a seductive place, isn't it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":20261,"text":"I don't live there."},{"time":21881,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":24454,"text":"But I did journey on a 27,000-mile trip"},{"time":30497,"text":"for two years, to the fastest-growing\nand whitest counties in America."}]},{"cues":[{"time":38732,"text":"What is a Whitopia?"},{"time":40820,"text":"I define Whitopia in three ways:"},{"time":43999,"text":"First, a Whitopia has posted at least\nsix percent population growth since 2000."},{"time":51451,"text":"Secondly, the majority of that growth\ncomes from white migrants."},{"time":56415,"text":"And third, the Whitopia\nhas an ineffable charm,"},{"time":60239,"text":"a pleasant look and feel,"},{"time":62818,"text":"a je Ne sais quoi."},{"time":64350,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":67583,"text":"To learn how and why\nWhitopias are ticking,"},{"time":71999,"text":"I immersed myself for several months\napiece in three of them:"},{"time":77446,"text":"first, St. George, Utah;"},{"time":80120,"text":"second, Coeur d'Alene, Idaho;"},{"time":82581,"text":"and third, Forsyth County, Georgia."}]},{"cues":[{"time":86883,"text":"First stop, St. George --\na beautiful town of red rock landscapes."},{"time":92433,"text":"In the 1850s, Brigham Young\ndispatched families to St. George"},{"time":97810,"text":"to grow cotton because\nof the hot, arid climate."},{"time":101118,"text":"And so they called it Utah's Dixie,\nand the name sticks to this day."},{"time":108368,"text":"I approached my time in each Whitopia\nlike an anthropologist."},{"time":113354,"text":"I made detailed spreadsheets of all\nthe power brokers in the communities,"},{"time":117999,"text":"who I needed to meet,\nwhere I needed to be,"},{"time":121457,"text":"and I threw myself with gusto\nin these communities."},{"time":124699,"text":"I went to zoning board meetings,"},{"time":126999,"text":"I went to Democratic clubs\nand Republican clubs."},{"time":130786,"text":"I went to poker nights."},{"time":135206,"text":"In St. George, I rented\na home at the Entrada,"},{"time":140142,"text":"one of the town's\npremier gated communities."},{"time":143278,"text":"There were no Motel 6's\nor Howard Johnsons for me."},{"time":147620,"text":"I lived in Whitopia as a resident,\nand not like a visitor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":152883,"text":"I rented myself this home by phone."},{"time":157409,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":159972,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":161361,"text":"Golf is the perfect seductive\nsymbol of Whitopia."},{"time":167750,"text":"When I went on my journey,"},{"time":169584,"text":"I had barely ever held a golf club."},{"time":172723,"text":"By the time I left, I was golfing\nat least three times a week."},{"time":177422,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":180133,"text":"Golf helps people bond."},{"time":183093,"text":"Some of the best interviews I ever scored\nduring my trip were on the golf courses."},{"time":189716,"text":"One venture capitalist, for example,\ninvited me to golf in his private club"},{"time":195199,"text":"that had no minority members."}]},{"cues":[{"time":198933,"text":"I also went fishing."},{"time":200432,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":202457,"text":"Because I had never fished,\nthis fellow had to teach me"},{"time":205497,"text":"how to cast my line and what bait to use."}]},{"cues":[{"time":210550,"text":"I also played poker every weekend."},{"time":213845,"text":"It was Texas Hold 'em with a $10 buy-in."},{"time":218058,"text":"My poker mates may have been bluffing\nabout the hands that they drew,"},{"time":222341,"text":"but they weren't bluffing\nabout their social beliefs."},{"time":225547,"text":"Some of the most raw,\nsalty conversations I ever had"},{"time":229174,"text":"during my journey were at the poker table."}]},{"cues":[{"time":232951,"text":"I'm a gung ho entertainer."},{"time":236140,"text":"I love to cook, I hosted\nmany dinner parties, and in return,"},{"time":240140,"text":"people invited me to their dinner parties,"},{"time":243312,"text":"and to their barbecues,\nand to their pool parties,"},{"time":245994,"text":"and to their birthday parties."}]},{"cues":[{"time":249385,"text":"But it wasn't all fun."},{"time":251781,"text":"Immigration turned out to be\na big issue in this Whitopia."},{"time":256167,"text":"The St. George's Citizens Council\non Illegal Immigration"},{"time":259605,"text":"held regular and active protests\nagainst immigration,"},{"time":263723,"text":"and so what I gleaned from this Whitopia\nis what a hot debate this would become."},{"time":269648,"text":"It was a real-time preview,\nand so it has become."}]},{"cues":[{"time":275084,"text":"Next stop: Almost Heaven,\na cabin I rented for myself"},{"time":280451,"text":"in Coeur d'Alene, in the beautiful\nNorth Idaho panhandle."},{"time":285048,"text":"I rented this place\nfor myself, also by phone."},{"time":288095,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":290530,"text":"The book \"A Thousand Places To See\nBefore You Die\" lists Coeur d'Alene --"},{"time":295374,"text":"it's a gorgeous paradise for huntsmen,\nboatmen and fishermen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":301031,"text":"My growing golf skills\ncame in handy in Coeur d'Alene."},{"time":304088,"text":"I golfed with retired LAPD cops."},{"time":307714,"text":"In 1993, around 11,000 families and cops"},{"time":313248,"text":"fled Los Angeles\nafter the L.A. racial unrest,"},{"time":319382,"text":"for North Idaho, and they've built\nan expatriated community."},{"time":324809,"text":"Given the conservatism of these cops,"},{"time":327846,"text":"there's no surprise that North Idaho\nhas a strong gun culture."},{"time":333212,"text":"In fact, it is said, North Idaho\nhas more gun dealers than gas stations."},{"time":341677,"text":"So what's a resident to do to fit in?"},{"time":344837,"text":"I hit the gun club."},{"time":346942,"text":"When I rented a gun,\nthe gentleman behind the counter"},{"time":350361,"text":"was perfectly pleasant and kind,"},{"time":352999,"text":"until I showed him\nmy New York City driver's license."},{"time":356999,"text":"That's when he got nervous."},{"time":359767,"text":"I'm not as bad a shot\nas I thought I might have been."}]},{"cues":[{"time":364448,"text":"What I learned from North Idaho\nis the peculiar brand of paranoia"},{"time":370928,"text":"that can permeate a community\nwhen so many cops and guns are around."}]},{"cues":[{"time":378070,"text":"In North Idaho, in my red pickup truck,"},{"time":382801,"text":"I kept a notepad."},{"time":384700,"text":"And in that notepad I counted\nmore Confederate flags than black people."},{"time":389589,"text":"In North Idaho, I found Confederate flags"},{"time":392876,"text":"on key chains, on cellphone paraphernalia,"},{"time":397125,"text":"and on cars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":399780,"text":"About a seven-minute drive\nfrom my hidden lake cabin"},{"time":403249,"text":"was the compound of Aryan Nations,"},{"time":406090,"text":"the white supremacist group."},{"time":410384,"text":"America's Promise Ministries,\nthe religious arm of Aryan Nations,"},{"time":415480,"text":"happened to have a three-day\nretreat during my visit."},{"time":420913,"text":"So I decided to crash it."},{"time":422572,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":425208,"text":"I'm the only non-Aryan journalist\nI'm aware of ever to have done so."},{"time":430067,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":431153,"text":"Among the many memorable\nepisodes of that retreat..."},{"time":435790,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":437083,"text":"...is when Abe, an Aryan,\nsidled up next to me."},{"time":440999,"text":"He slapped my knee, and he said, \"Hey\nRich, I just want you to know one thing."},{"time":446443,"text":"We are not white supremacists.\nWe are white separatists."},{"time":450967,"text":"We don't think we're better than you,"},{"time":452865,"text":"we just want to be away from you.\""},{"time":454578,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":459016,"text":"Indeed, most white people in Whitopia\nare neither white supremacists"},{"time":466035,"text":"or white separatists;"},{"time":467874,"text":"in fact, they're not there\nfor explicitly racial reasons at all."},{"time":472140,"text":"Rather, they emigrate there"},{"time":475220,"text":"for friendliness, comfort,\nsecurity, safety --"},{"time":478952,"text":"reasons that they implicitly associate\nto whiteness in itself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":485064,"text":"Next stop was Georgia."},{"time":488224,"text":"In Georgia, I stayed in an exurb\nnorth of Atlanta."},{"time":493027,"text":"In Utah, I found poker;"},{"time":494846,"text":"in Idaho, I found guns;"},{"time":496561,"text":"in Georgia, I found God."},{"time":498139,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":499402,"text":"The way that I immersed myself\nin this Whitopia"},{"time":502999,"text":"was to become active\nat First Redeemer Church,"},{"time":506414,"text":"a megachurch that's so huge\nthat it has golf carts"},{"time":509942,"text":"to escort the congregants around\nits many parking lots on campus."},{"time":515758,"text":"I was active in the youth ministry."},{"time":518491,"text":"And for me, personally,\nI was more comfortable in this Whitopia"},{"time":523447,"text":"than say, in a Colorado, or an Idaho,\nor even a suburban Boston."},{"time":528999,"text":"That is because [there], in Georgia,"},{"time":532113,"text":"white people and black people are more\nhistorically familiar to one another."},{"time":537092,"text":"I was less exotic in this Whitopia."},{"time":539912,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":542684,"text":"But what does it all mean?"},{"time":545042,"text":"Whitopian dreaming, Whitopia migration,\nis a push-pull phenomenon,"},{"time":550447,"text":"full of alarming pushes\nand alluring pulls,"},{"time":554612,"text":"and Whitopia operates at the level\nof conscious and unconscious bias."},{"time":561860,"text":"It's possible for people to be in Whitopia\nnot for racist reasons,"},{"time":567287,"text":"though it has racist outcomes."},{"time":571704,"text":"Many Whitopians feel pushed by illegals,"},{"time":575572,"text":"social welfare abuse, minorities,\ndensity, crowded schools."},{"time":581113,"text":"Many Whitopians feel pulled by merit,"},{"time":586316,"text":"freedom, the allure of privatism --\nprivatized places, privatized people,"},{"time":592104,"text":"privatized things."},{"time":595524,"text":"And I learned in Whitopia\nhow a country can have racism"},{"time":601136,"text":"without racists."}]},{"cues":[{"time":603241,"text":"Many of my smug urban liberal friends"},{"time":606052,"text":"couldn't believe I would go\non such a venture."},{"time":609447,"text":"The reality is that many white Americans\nare affable and kind."},{"time":615643,"text":"Interpersonal race relations --\nhow we treat each other as human beings --"},{"time":620436,"text":"are vastly better than in\nmy parents' generation."},{"time":625162,"text":"Can you imagine me going\nto Whitopia 40 years ago?"},{"time":629596,"text":"What a journey that would have been."},{"time":631508,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":633290,"text":"And yet, some things haven't changed."},{"time":635572,"text":"America is as residentially\nand educationally segregated today"},{"time":642307,"text":"as it was in 1970."}]},{"cues":[{"time":647523,"text":"As Americans, we often find ways\nto cook for each other,"},{"time":652178,"text":"to dance with each other,"},{"time":653822,"text":"to host with each other,"},{"time":655719,"text":"but why can't that translate into how we\ntreat each other as communities?"},{"time":661235,"text":"It's a devastating irony,"},{"time":663379,"text":"how we have gone forward as individuals,"},{"time":666715,"text":"and backwards as communities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":671766,"text":"One of the Whitopian outlooks\nthat really hit me"},{"time":676083,"text":"was a proverbial saying:"},{"time":678279,"text":"\"One black man is\na delightful dinner guest;"},{"time":681779,"text":"50 black men is a ghetto.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":688879,"text":"One of the big contexts animating\nmy Whitopian journey was the year 2042."},{"time":696668,"text":"By 2042, white people will no longer be\nthe American majority."},{"time":703450,"text":"As such, will there be more Whitopias?"},{"time":708926,"text":"In looking at this,"},{"time":710637,"text":"the danger of Whitopia is\nthat the more segregation we have,"},{"time":717368,"text":"the less we can look at and confront\nconscious and unconscious bias."}]},{"cues":[{"time":726304,"text":"I ventured on my two-year,\n27,000 mile journey"},{"time":730689,"text":"to learn where, why, and how\nwhite people are fleeing,"},{"time":735800,"text":"but I didn't expect to have\nso much fun on my journey."},{"time":738566,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":739597,"text":"I didn't expect to learn\nso much about myself."},{"time":743408,"text":"I don't expect I'll be living\nin a Whitopia --"},{"time":746880,"text":"or a Blacktopia, for that matter."},{"time":749792,"text":"I do plan to continue golfing\nevery chance I get."},{"time":753225,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":754811,"text":"And I'll just have to leave the guns\nand megachurches back in Whitopia."}]},{"cues":[{"time":760714,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":761890,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}